12/07/2005
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Kai Eide, UN special envoy for the review of democratic standards implementation on Kosovo, met on Monday (11 July) with Serbia-Montenegro Foreign Minister Vuk Draskovic and Serbian Prime Minister Vojislav Kostunica.
Eide said there must be more progress and engagement by all political groups, in order to achieve a multiethnic Kosovo.
Draskovic stressed the need for Serbs to participate in Kosovo institutions, while Kostunica emphasised that the decentralisation of Kosovo is crucial.
On Tuesday, Eide meets with Serbian President Boris Tadic, South Serbia Co-ordination Centre head Nebojsa Covic and federal Human Rights Minister Rasim Ljajic.
In other news, Serbian Justice Minister Zoran Stojkovic met with OSCE Mission Chief in Serbia-Montenegro Maurizio Massari to discuss the pace of judicial reforms in Serbia.
Stojkovic said the Venetian Convention and the Council of Europe would assist his ministry with implementing its strategy.
(RTS, B92, Tanjug, Serbian Government Web site - 11/07/05)
